<paragraph id="031DD2692C15C1218CACABDA58297FD3" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EA3EE7064F06E86B25DEF2E386515B07" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="D46E4805AC1A67FE6C6AC31CF3D55B20" authorityName="S. Y. Zhang" authorityYear="2021" class="Polychaeta" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Lycoris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lycoris wulingensis" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="wulingensis">
<emphasis id="CB4DC95EF4D8E003A5FF83A9CBA02E37" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Lycoris wulingensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in the east of Wuling Mountains and its surrounding areas, such as Cili, Linli, Li, Taoyuan and Yongding Counties (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="DB76782CF968FC6EC3A61ED4C7F7E50C" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Distribution map of Lycoris wulingensis S. Y. Zhang and its related species." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.177.62741.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/534137" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CECAC0950804D0408E4D0A7618DD3211" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="habitat">
<paragraph id="A66F593C620F604D2A59486FB59E588E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9FCA118F5103CC34166F1392F56E534A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="8E2F147F2D5538E390E8499FA27C5DAC" authorityName="S. Y. Zhang" authorityYear="2021" class="Polychaeta" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Lycoris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lycoris wulingensis" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="wulingensis">
<emphasis id="16E6A590380D1CCE07827D12F5383051" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Lycoris wulingensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is partial to grow on the edge of forest roads, farmland or riverside beaches, usually under deciduous trees (such as 
<taxonomicName id="E04412EB471E676AE8F1CAF23889DE6E" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Alangiaceae" genus="Alangium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Alangium chinense" order="Umbelliflorae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="chinense">
<emphasis id="1AF98E453EE03FC6FE6F461DA4FFBAE7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Alangium chinense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="9B79B3C66DE3FF4A6797E389B081F418" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Juglandaceae" genus="Pterocarya" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pterocarya stenoptera" order="Juglandales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="stenoptera">
<emphasis id="EAED24A3B7E59AF636FAFB8206DE20F1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pterocarya stenoptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and accompanied by 
<taxonomicName id="6DC138F0B5E4136EFADCB58976740556" class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Araceae" genus="Pinellia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pinellia ternata" order="Spathiflorae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="ternata">
<emphasis id="C95B4592600FC639F86F4AAC46014D3C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pinellia ternata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="9049D0742A68A0B8A2EF8376B2E7005C" class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Commelinaceae" genus="Commelina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Commelina communis" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="communis">
<emphasis id="56B54E814B4EAFE98EFECFFCC3DE2F9A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Commelina communis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E03737B6360571851C88148BADC6B48A" class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Poaceae" genus="Arthraxon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Arthraxon hispidus" order="Graminales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="hispidus">
<emphasis id="74BA9451F598DA20ACCECAD8EFDA4C4D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Arthraxon hispidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="DC5FDFA3F7EDEA2AC040AA01EE49A50C" class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Liliaceae" genus="Ophiopogon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ophiopogon bodinieri" order="Liliiflorae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="bodinieri">
<emphasis id="6EF33B4DA0F360FE601842BD3BF8A460" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ophiopogon bodinieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
etc. The surrounding residents sometimes cultivate it as an ornamental plant.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
